edit: Venath 1242185163
subject: Bug/Idea/typo etiquette
message:
   After going through our rather lengthy roster of issues...  Some 381
altogether, I've noticed certain rather annoying trends that most people
commit when trying to report their bug/idea/typo.  So to prevent your issue
from being ignored or outright deleted, please take the following steps to
insure yourself against such an event.

Step 1:
When reporting a typo/bug/idea, please be in the exact room that is relevant
to the issue.  Our bug-tracking system reports the room in which you submit
your issue, so it is crucial that the room be the one with the problem.

Step 2:
When reporting bugs/typos, try to be as detailed as you can with what
the actual problem is.  Saying something like "this mob has a bad description"
doesn't exactly help us know what you mean.  Sure we can figure it out
eventually, but the longer we take to figure it out, the less likely it is
that it will be fixed.

Step 3:
DON'T WASTE OUR TIME WITH SPAM!  We will delete/purge/freeze or feed you to
dragons.  Well, maybe not that severe, but seriously.  Don't tell us hi on
bug/typo/idea.  Don't tell us we're doing a horrible job.  Don't tell us that
we have smelly feet!  Don't tell us we should get bent, or dunk our heads in
ice water.  It's all very much a waste of our time, and smothers the real
issues in spam.  So please, refrain from unnecessary messages.

In addition to those, players should know which category to pick when
reporting their issue.  Bug/typo/idea.  They are ALL different, and need to be
treated as such.

Bug:
Anything that has to do with the programming code, or scripting language.  
The scripting language is what is used to run our quests, so if the quest is
obviously broken, then that's a bug.  If an emote is giving weird messages,
that's a programming bug.  If a door is not working properly, that is also a
bug, but only a very slight one.  But still use bug.  

Typo:
Use this issue report function when you want to report a grammatical or
spelling error in a description, or quest speech, or whatever.  If it's
spelled wrong, or put in the wrong part of a sentance, use this to report it.
Just be sure to tell us exactly where the typo is so that we know where to
look.  If you had a hard time finding that typo, chances are we're going to
have the same hard time if not harder.  So be precice.  

Idea:
This is where you report your ideas that we will most likely end up
ignoring.  This is not because your ideas are horrible, terrible, stupid,
etc...  No, we'll probably not implement your ideas because we're lazy, and
are working on more important things.  It should come as no shock to anyone
that 99% of the ideas submitted are thrown out immediately due to being...  
Well...  Stupid.  The remaining 1% that are deemed to have any merit are
usually ignored for a year before someone works on them.  So with that in
mind, please please please please PLEASE try to make your ideas good!  If you
think for one second that your idea won't ever be considered because it sounds
stupid to you, then do us all a favor.  DON'T SUBMIT IT!  For instance...  If
something has been removed from the game, chances are we're not bringing it
back.  Like the area "Dark Abbey".  That zone is removed until someone goes in
and fixes it all up and makes it pretty and balanced.  Until then, DON'T ask
us to bring it back.  It's not going to happen.  Same goes for permastone
enhanced objects.  Not happening.  Vaporform...  NOT HAPPENING!  If you would
like us to discuss your idea with you, then submit it on the forums.  It would
be alot easier for us to tell you why we're not going to accept your idea
there.  Or maybe flesh out that idea a little.


Please keep in mind that there are very few active deities, and as such, our
workload is, to say the VERY least, immense.  With that in mind, take the long
paragraphs above with a grain of salt, and understand that we are not getting
paid for this.  Well...  Maybe Zzur is...  But the rest of us aren't.  :P

If you get nothing else out of this post, at least get this.  Don't spam us
with your nonsense!  But don't be scared away from submitting real issues that
need to be fixed.  Most of them are genuine, but please don't drown those out
in nonsense.  In this case, try to have a little empathy with the gods.  We
are, after all, trying to make this game a better and more interesting place.
Don't demoralize us with wasted time.

-Venath
~
