poster: Laoris
time: 1242442325
subject: Re: Venath wrt bug/idea/typo etiquette
message:
While I must agree that some idea/bug submissions are obnoxious (such as "bob
is so nice", "green", and "does this give you laryngitis?"), I would say that
the vast majority of them are quite legitimate.
 
We do pay attention to each bug and idea submitted, and very few get thrown
away.  When we do reject an idea, it is usually because either it would be
terribly difficult for us to implement or we think it would unnecessarily
disrupt what balance we have in the game.
 
I will admit that we coders frequently do not have enough time to do all the
things we would like to.  We each have our own pet projects, and time
available for coding must get divided between working on our own ideas,
implementing player ideas, and fixing bugs.  Sometimes bugs and ideas are
easy to resolve, and other times they take an eternity (for instance, I've been
working on a fix for the crash bug with clans for the last two days).
 
I guess I'm asking for patience when it comes to bugs and ideas; don't
let us slack off though.  Please don't submit duplicate reports, but
feel free to remind us if you feel that an issue is going unaddressed.
Don't be afraid to submit any serious ideas, either!
 
-Lao
~
